All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants, NetworkServiceEventListener
public class ServerMainFrame
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements NetworkServiceEventListener

A frame which allows a user to configure, start, and monitor for a database file network service, it can manage only one service at time.

It consist of three parts:

  • Network service configuration entries: capture user entries for configuring network service which are database file path, service name, and service port.
  • Network service statistics display: displays start and stop statistics for network service.
  • Actions bar: contains actions for starting and stopping a network service
User configuration entries are loaded and persisted using AdminPref instance, persisting for those entries is only done for successfully started network service by calling PrefBean.flush().
This frame uses EngineService.createNetworkService(java.io.File, java.lang.String, int) to create a network service for a database file. An implementation for engine service is loaded through EngineServiceLoader.locateEngineService() factory method.
Once a network service is started successfully, configuration entries will be disabled until the network service is stopped.

Author:
Mohammad S. Abdellatif
See Also:
EngineServiceLoader, EngineService, NetworkService, AdminPref, Serialized Form
